        <p class="lead">
          Searching for a Google Ads management agency in Ahmedabad puts you in front of dozens of options, all claiming to be experts, all promising page one results and guaranteed leads. The reality is that Google Ads management quality varies enormously, and a poorly managed campaign can waste Rs 50,000 in a month without a single qualified lead. This guide gives you a framework to evaluate any agency objectively before you spend a rupee.
        </p>

        <h2 id="why-management-matters">Why professional Google Ads management matters in Ahmedabad</h2>
        <p>
          Google Ads is not a platform you can set up once and leave running. The Ahmedabad market has specific dynamics that require active management:
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Competition is rising:</strong> More Ahmedabad businesses have shifted ad spend online since 2022. In competitive categories like real estate, legal services, clinics, and home services, cost per click has risen 30 to 50% in three years. Without continuous bid optimisation and negative keyword management, your budget erodes fast.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Search behaviour is local and fragmented:</strong> An Ahmedabad user searching "dentist near me" from Satellite is different from one searching from Maninagar. Proper geo-targeting, ad scheduling around peak hours (7am to 10am and 6pm to 9pm for most B2C services), and device bid adjustments are essential. These are not set-it-and-forget-it configurations.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Conversion tracking is broken on most accounts:</strong> In our experience reviewing accounts taken over from other agencies, more than half have either no conversion tracking or incorrectly configured tracking. This means the algorithm is optimising for clicks and impressions, not leads, because it has no signal about what a "good outcome" looks like. Fixing this alone typically reduces cost per lead by 20 to 40%.
        </p>

        <h2 id="seven-questions">7 questions to ask before hiring a Google Ads agency in Ahmedabad</h2>

        <p><strong>1. Are you a Google Partner or do you have current Google Ads certification?</strong></p>
        <p>
          Google Partner status means the agency has passed Google's certification exams, manages a minimum spend threshold, and maintains performance standards. It is not a guarantee of quality, but uncertified agencies managing significant budgets is a red flag. Ask to see the badge or certification directly, not just a claim on their website.
        </p>

        <p><strong>2. How will you set up and verify conversion tracking before the campaign launches?</strong></p>
        <p>
          This is the single most important question. Any agency that does not mention conversion tracking in the first conversation is either inexperienced or does not care about your results. Proper conversion tracking should capture phone calls (both from ads and from the website), form submissions, and WhatsApp clicks at minimum. Ask them to walk you through exactly how they will set this up.
        </p>

        <p><strong>3. What is your keyword research process and how do you handle negative keywords?</strong></p>
        <p>
          Broad match keywords in Ahmedabad without a robust negative keyword list will trigger your ads for completely irrelevant searches. Ask the agency to show you an example negative keyword list from an existing client in your industry. An agency that has never built one, or uses only 10 to 20 negatives, is not managing bids properly.
        </p>

        <p><strong>4. How will you report results, and what metrics will you focus on?</strong></p>
        <p>
          Any agency can report impressions and clicks. What you need to see is: cost per conversion, conversion rate, and return on ad spend (ROAS) or cost per lead. If an agency leads with CTR and impression share but cannot tell you cost per lead from last month's campaigns for another client, they are hiding behind vanity metrics.
        </p>

        <p><strong>5. Who will actually manage my account day to day?</strong></p>
        <p>
          Many agencies in Ahmedabad sell on the strength of their founders and senior team, then hand accounts to junior executives with 6 months of experience. Ask specifically who will touch your account and how many accounts that person manages. More than 15 to 20 active accounts per manager is a warning sign for quality.
        </p>

        <p><strong>6. What is your policy if my campaign underperforms in the first 60 days?</strong></p>
        <p>
          A good agency will have a structured review process: week 2 performance check, month 1 optimisation report, month 2 strategy adjustment. If an agency says "Google Ads takes time, give us 6 months" without committing to any specific interim reviews, they are covering for poor management with vague timelines.
        </p>

        <p><strong>7. What is your fee structure, and how is it tied to my ad spend?</strong></p>
        <p>
          Percentage-of-spend models (typically 15 to 20% of monthly ad budget) create a conflict of interest: the agency makes more money if you spend more, not if you get better results. Flat monthly management fees are more aligned with your interests. At DC technolabs, we charge a flat management fee regardless of your ad spend level.
        </p>

        <div class="mid-cta">
          <span class="mid-cta-tag">Free campaign review</span>
          <h3>Not happy with your current Google Ads results?</h3>
          <p>We review your existing Google Ads account for free, identify what is wasting budget, and show you what a properly managed campaign looks like. No obligation.</p>
          <a href="/services/google-ads/" class="btn btn-white btn-sm">Get a free Ads audit</a>
        </div>

        <h2 id="red-flags">Red flags from Google Ads agencies in Ahmedabad</h2>
        <p>
          These patterns come up repeatedly when businesses switch to us from other agencies:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>They own your Google Ads account:</strong> Your account should be under your own Google account. An agency that creates the account in their name and does not give you admin access can hold your campaign history hostage. Always insist on admin access from day one.</li>
          <li><strong>Guaranteed rankings or guaranteed leads:</strong> Google Ads results depend on many variables: your offer, your landing page, your industry competition, seasonality. No legitimate agency guarantees a specific number of leads.</li>
          <li><strong>Using only broad match keywords:</strong> Broad match without proper negative keyword management burns budget on irrelevant clicks. If an agency cannot explain the difference between broad, phrase, and exact match, do not hire them.</li>
          <li><strong>No landing page recommendations:</strong> Sending Ads traffic to your homepage instead of a dedicated, conversion-optimised landing page typically cuts conversion rates by 50 to 70%. An agency that does not raise this issue early is not thinking about your results.</li>
          <li><strong>Reports only on ad platform data, not business outcomes:</strong> Clicks are not leads. Impressions are not revenue. If your monthly report does not show how many phone calls and form submissions came from your ads, the agency is not measuring what matters.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="pricing">Google Ads management pricing in Ahmedabad</h2>
        <p>
          There are two costs to understand: your ad spend (what you pay Google directly) and the agency management fee.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Ad spend budget:</strong> For most service businesses in Ahmedabad, Rs 15,000 to Rs 30,000 per month is the starting range to generate meaningful lead volume. Competitive industries like real estate, law, hospitals, and immigration consultants need Rs 40,000 to Rs 1,00,000 per month to compete at the top of results. Your agency should recommend a budget based on your cost-per-click research, not a round number.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Agency management fees:</strong> Expect Rs 8,000 to Rs 25,000 per month from a reputable Ahmedabad agency. Be cautious of agencies charging below Rs 5,000 per month for active management — this is not enough to cover the hours required to manage a campaign properly. Similarly, be cautious of percentage-of-spend models that scale fees automatically with your budget.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>What DC technolabs charges:</strong> Our Google Ads management starts at Rs 10,000 per month for campaigns with ad spend up to Rs 50,000/month. There are no percentage-of-spend add-ons, no setup fees for standard campaigns, and we provide monthly performance reports with full transparency on what your budget produced.
        </p>

        <h2 id="what-good-looks-like">What good Google Ads management looks like in practice</h2>
        <p>
          For an Ahmedabad interior design firm we manage, the account looked like this when we took it over: Rs 40,000/month ad spend, 1,200 clicks/month, 8 leads/month, cost per lead Rs 5,000. Six months later: Rs 35,000/month ad spend, 980 clicks/month, 38 leads/month, cost per lead Rs 920. The change was not a bigger budget. It was fixing conversion tracking, cutting irrelevant keywords, restructuring campaigns by service type, building a dedicated landing page for each service, and tightening geo-targeting to the areas where their clients actually live.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is what proper Google Ads management in Ahmedabad looks like: lower cost per lead, not just more impressions.
        </p>

        <h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>

        <h3 id="faq-cost">How much does Google Ads management cost in Ahmedabad?</h3>
        <p>
          Google Ads management in Ahmedabad typically costs Rs 8,000 to Rs 25,000 per month in agency fees, separate from your ad spend budget. At DC technolabs, management starts at Rs 10,000/month. Your ad spend budget depends on your industry and competition — most Ahmedabad businesses start with Rs 15,000 to Rs 50,000/month in ad spend.
        </p>

        <h3 id="faq-results">What results should I expect from Google Ads in Ahmedabad?</h3>
        <p>
          With proper management, Ahmedabad businesses typically see leads starting within 48 to 72 hours of campaign launch. A well-optimised campaign delivers a cost per lead of Rs 300 to Rs 1,500 depending on the industry. Campaigns improve meaningfully over the first 60 days as Google's algorithm optimises for your best-converting keywords and audiences.
        </p>

        <h3 id="faq-how-to-evaluate">How do I know if my Google Ads agency is doing a good job?</h3>
        <p>
          A good Google Ads agency provides monthly reports showing: total spend, impressions, clicks, CTR, cost per click, conversions (calls and form fills), cost per conversion, and Quality Score trends. If your agency cannot tell you your cost per lead or has not set up conversion tracking, they are not managing your account properly.
        </p>

        <h3 id="faq-min-budget">What is the minimum ad budget for Google Ads in Ahmedabad?</h3>
        <p>
          For most service businesses in Ahmedabad, Rs 15,000 per month in ad spend is the practical minimum to get meaningful data and leads. Below Rs 10,000/month, the data is too thin to optimise effectively. Competitive industries like real estate, legal, and healthcare need Rs 40,000 to Rs 80,000/month in ad spend to compete for top positions.
        </p>

        <h3 id="faq-freelancer-vs-agency">Should I hire a Google Ads freelancer or agency in Ahmedabad?</h3>
        <p>
          A freelancer can work for simple campaigns with small budgets under Rs 20,000/month. For campaigns above Rs 30,000/month, or for competitive industries, a dedicated agency with a full team manages risk better and usually delivers lower cost per lead. Always verify if they are Google Partners with active certification before hiring.
        </p>

